    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey can u explain why my muscles feel like they're burning when i do sprints? like what's actually happening biologically when that stinging feeling starts?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When you sprint, your muscles feel burned due to lactic acid accumulation and muscle damage from anaerobic exercise. Lactic acid is a byproduct of anaerobic respiration, a process that occurs when your muscles don't have enough oxygen to convert glucose into energy. As your muscles fatigue, they shift to anaerobic respiration, producing lactic acid, leading to the characteristic burning sensation. This sensation is usually temporary and can be managed with recovery and hydration.",
